oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Montreux Atlanta Music Festival (September 5) (green)
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Musical instruments; King, Albert; King, Jimmie; Guitar;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: One color window card (purple on green paper) Hatch poster announcing the Montreux Atlanta Music Festival 1993, a tribute to Albert King, at Piedmont Park featuring Luther "Guitar Jr" Johnson, Little Jimmy King, Tinsley Ellis, Ann Peebles, Lary "Arkansas" Davis, Pops Staples, and Little Milton. Poster features woodcut of a guitar.
